John, your question has had books written, and opinions offered by better thinkers then I. Almost Supreme Court Bork's Book is good, I am told. As a child of the 60's, and I mean full blooded wild in the streets free love and drugs protest &quot;child&quot; of the 60's, now with two kids of my own, I have given long thought to why society today is so bad. Why unwed mothers are so high, both in numbers and crack, why political correctness is so &quot;in&quot; yet so cancerous. The NAACP called for a Ban on Websters Dictionary today, did you read or hear about that, seems they don't like the N word being in the dictionary. Even though Websters calls it the most derogatory racist slur, and also has the slur words for every other race and minority group, political correctness is at work again.<br><br>
P.C. I think is one of the main forces destroying America. We have a President who is totally under its control. And a Congress.  Thats strike one.  The breakdown of the American family structure and the fact of individual responsibility avoidance is strike two. Strike one and two both have their roots in the 60's and the &quot;counter culture&quot;.<br><br>
Well the counter culture of the Grateful Deadheads and &quot;a few hits on the bong won't hurt you&quot; mentality has now become mainstream, and fucking up the generation of our parents, of Wally and Beaver, Lucy and Ricky, and Waltons Mountain. <br><br>
All young kids (high school) need to strike out due to hormones and to establish their identities, but the problem is the 60's generation used most of them up.  That is why, in my opinion (you asked), the likes of gothic rock, Marilyn Manson (oy vey), Corn, and the screaming rage of the pimple set is so trendy. Calvin Klien and his Heroin chic ad's just feeds into that.  We have become a culture feeding on itself,and one that can not continue on this way. Hence the rise of the Christian right, Militias, and others, who want to turn the clock back, but can't.<br><br>
Does this all relate to the military you ask of me, a C.O.? and I say YES. I think even drafting everyone after high school, for a 2 year stint, in the armed forces or the peace corp, job corp,  but with military stictness and training, might turn this country around. (surprised?)  That and the military occupation of most inner cities, would be a start.<br><br>
There are just two many young people out there raising themselves, while the &quot;mature&quot; adults play political correctness games, sexual harrassment games, and &quot;who can we sue today&quot; games.<br><br>
Thanks John, I feel much better now.  Bill me for a consult.<br>
